description: This compound belongs to the class of inorganic compounds known as lanthanide nitrates. These are inorganic compounds in which the largest oxoanion is nitrate, and in which the heaviest atom not in an oxoanion is a lanthanide.

direct_parent.description: Inorganic compounds in which the largest oxoanion is nitrate, and in which the heaviest atom not in an oxoanion is a lanthanide.
direct_parent.name: Lanthanide nitrates

kingdom.description: Compounds that do not contain a C atom. Exceptions are made for isocyanide/cyanide and their non-hydrocarbyl derivatives, thiophosgene, carbon diselenide, carbon monosulfide, carbon disulfide, carbon subsulfide, carbon monoxide, carbon trioxide, carbon suboxide, and dicarbon monoxide.
kingdom.name: Inorganic compounds
